<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-06T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="469" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1033: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-06T22:00:00-02:00">February 6, 1933—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 6—7:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>12. Prior to the receipt of the Department’s 20, February 6, 3 p.m., I
                            had conveyed to the Minister for Foreign Affairs the substance of
                            Secretary White’s conversation with Thurston. He stated that Brazil has
                            not abandoned mediation but will not accept the Peruvian proposal with
                            respect to long tenure of Leticia.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>